  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p/>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands, <lb/>OFFICE 4th DIVISION, 9th SUB-DISTRICT,
     VIRGINIA
     <name type="recipient">Mr. Joseph Milsted</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1867-06-04">June 4, 1867</date>
      <name type="place">Augusta Co</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Sir</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>Peyton Harris (c) complains of bad treatment of his child by your wife and that you attempt
     to break an agreement made with him for present year. I need not tell you that the law gives
     you no right to beat or threaten anyone and before you can put Harris out of his house
     &amp; garden you must assign sufficient reason, such as breach of agreement on his part. </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Yr Obt Srv</salute>
     <signed>Thos. P. Jackson <lb/> Agent</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
